    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="5">
            <title>CONTROL VALVE</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302909">Figure 9</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302909" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302909" filename="../figg13/G1302909.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Control Valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the two air lines at the "S" or Supply Port and "P" or End Port of the slave
                    valve on the transmission case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302910">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302910" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302910" filename="../figg13/G1302910.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10. Disconnect Air Lines</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If desired, the gear shift lever housing assembly can now be removed from the shifter housing
                        by removing the four bolts from the tower.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two mounting screws in the Roadranger valve cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302911">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302911" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302911" filename="../figg13/G1302911.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11. Remove Mounting Screws</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the cover down the shift lever to expose the valve ports and disconnect the two
                    air lines (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302912">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302912" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302912" filename="../figg13/G1302912.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Disconnect Air Lines</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the jam nut and turn the valve and nut from the gear shift lever (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302913">Figure 13</hotlnk>). Remove the valve cover, air lines, sheathing and
                    O-rings from the lever.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302913" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302913" filename="../figg13/G1302913.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13. Turn Valve and Nut From Gear Shift Lever</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
